{"id":35014,"date":"2018-08-23T08:42:45","date_gmt":"2018-08-23T12:42:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/blog-v2.sweeten.com\/?p=35014"},"modified":"2023-07-04T05:25:16","modified_gmt":"2023-07-04T09:25:16","slug":"brooklyn-grandparents-renovate-kensington","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/sweeten-renovations\/entire-home-renovations\/brooklyn-grandparents-renovate-kensington\/","title":{"rendered":"A Grandparent Renovation Story: Coming Home to Stay in Brooklyn"},"content":{"rendered":"<h2>For two Brooklyn grandparents with aging-in-place plans, a layout change turns their co-op into an oasis<\/h2>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-07.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35016 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"kitchen\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-07-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout, Brooklyn grandparents renovate\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Marie and John are both NYC natives\u00a0who had\u00a0lived in the suburbs of Washington, D.C.\u00a0for many years. When their first grandchild was born in Brooklyn in 2014, they began plotting the move back to their hometown.\u00a0After John retired in 2017, the couple decided to buy a home that would accommodate large gatherings with their friends, five children, and the growing number of grandkids.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35478 size-chrono\" title=\"Marie and John\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-22-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Marie and John, Brooklyn grandparents, home renovation, home, design construction\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-Floorplan.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-Floorplan.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35017 size-chrono\" title=\"floor plan \" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-Floorplan-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-01.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35019 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"living room\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-01-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, living room, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After a four-month search with unsuccessful bids on two other properties, Marie and John visited an open house in the Kensington neighborhood of Brooklyn. \u201cEven though it was a very wet, snowy day in early 2017, there were many potential buyers,\u201d Marie said. &#8220;We both liked the size and layout\u00a0and could see great potential in the space. There were 12 large windows with three exposures, which won us over. We ended up paying over asking price, but were satisfied with the deal.\u201d The 3-bed, 1.5-bath co-op boasted about 1,300 square feet of living space and was close to Prospect Park as well as their children. The closing occurred in May; the couple <a href=\"https:\/\/app.sweeten.com\/projects\/22838\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">turned to Sweeten<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/app.sweeten.com\/members\/2425\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">found a Sweeten architect<\/a>\u00a0to help with a thorough renovation.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-01.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35024 size-chrono\" title=\"before\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-01-723x933.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, living room, design, renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"933\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-02.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35021 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"living room\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-02-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, living room, design, renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although serviceable, the apartment needed some TLC in terms of remodeling the kitchen, bathroom, and\u00a0converting an existing half-bath into a master bath with a shower. They also wanted to open up the space so that the three exposures could bring light into every corner of the apartment. The conversation with their Sweeten architect resulted in architectural renderings, which planned the space as an &#8220;age-in-place oasis&#8221;\u00a0for\u00a0the active couple who\u00a0wanted the convenience and amenities of city living while also being able to host a large extended family.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-05.gif\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35023 size-chrono\" title=\"french doors\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-05.gif\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, french doors, sliding doors, living room\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-03.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35022 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"living room\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-03-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, living room, design, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To accommodate the couple\u2019s desire to age in place and ultimately remain in the apartment as long as possible, their architect added accessible design features in the bathrooms. Materials and design were also implemented for easy maintenance, such as closets to keep spaces clutter-free, large-scale bath ceramic tile that required less grout, and moisture- and heat-resistant Caesarstone kitchen countertops.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-03.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-03.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35025 size-chrono\" title=\"before\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-03-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a>(<em>Befores above<\/em>) Dining room cabinets replaced the closets (l.); kitchen entry located to the right. The wall was removed.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35026 size-chrono\" title=\"dining room\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout, dining room\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11-723x482.jpg 723w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11-585x390.jpg 585w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-11.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 723px) 100vw, 723px\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-12.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35027 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"dining room\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-12-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout, dining room\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the common spaces, a reconfigured layout maximized the open space for entertaining and cooking. A windowed den was previously accessible through the kitchen, but a reorientation\u00a0connected it to the living room, which made more sense. The den could double as a guest room when necessary but would serve as a corner office on a daily basis. The pocket doors, which created an opening of six feet,\u00a0could be left open so that more natural light entered the living room.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-05.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35031 size-chrono\" title=\"before\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-05-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-13.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35028 size-chrono\" title=\"kitchen\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-13-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-16.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35030 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"kitchen\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-16-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, kitchen renovation, open layout\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The kitchen, which previously had a tile floor, was re-laid with <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/gallery\/product-101\/hardwood-flooring-how-to-choose\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">hardwood<\/a> to match that in the living room. The new continuous flooring helped unify the now open-plan living area. \u201cOur new kitchen was outfitted with gray IKEA Bodbyn cabinets and glossy deep crimson glass tiles for the backsplash. It\u2019s the extra special spark to our gray kitchen,\u201d Marie said. The tall upper cabinets take advantage of the high ceiling and provide extra storage space. &#8220;Based on our own past experience, we chose quartz countertops,&#8221; she added. &#8220;The fact that it is practically indestructible met our desire for a low-maintenance lifestyle.\u201d<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The demolition of a wall between the kitchen and the dining alcove transformed the previously dark space into a brightly lit and well-integrated dining area. Their Sweeten architect also replaced the existing closets at the back of the dining space with additional cabinetry that matched the kitchen. Upper cabinets were faced with glass and a mirrored backsplash\u00a0which the homeowners loved. A spherical chandelier in bronze was hung\u00a0above the dining table as a statement piece.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-08.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35035 size-chrono\" title=\"before\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-08-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, bathroom renovation, before\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-19.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35033 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"bathroom\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-19-723x1085.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, bathroom renovation\" width=\"723\" height=\"1085\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The next major transformation was in the master bath, which was originally a powder room (they planned to borrowed square footage from a second bedroom). The tiny space had no room for a shower, which the homeowners wanted, so the architect embarked on an arduous process of convincing the co-op board that increasing the footprint of the bathroom, which involved creating wet-over-dry conditions (something that\u2019s usually a no-no for co-ops), would not be a problem.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-20.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35032 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"bathroom\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-20-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, bathroom, renovation, shower, toilet, Brooklyn grandparents\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In order to allay the concerns of the board, the architect met with the board and building engineer to go over all of the precautions that would be taken as well as the materials that were chosen and installation methods. The result of their architect&#8217;s perseverance: excellent water- and sound-proofing so that neighboring apartments would not be affected.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">They chose light-colored <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/gallery\/reno-notebook\/10-bathroom-floor-tiles\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">tile for the floors<\/a> and walls, with accent tiles for the shower floor and niche.\u00a0The design included a long safety bar inside the shower for more stability when showering\u2014one of the features that would accommodate Marie and John as they age. A large square sink from Duravit sits on a stand with modern lines and one shelf below.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-07.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35034 size-chrono\" title=\"before\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-BEFORE-07-723x482.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, bathroom renovation, before, Brooklyn grandparents\" width=\"723\" height=\"482\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><br \/>\n<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-17.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35036 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"bathroom\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-17-723x1085.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, bathroom renovation, floating vanity, bathtub, Brooklyn grandparents\" width=\"723\" height=\"1085\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The guest bath featured a large mirror with a stone shelf beneath and lighter colors. Safety handlebars were also added to the inside of the bathtub wall. For easy cleaning and to free up the floor space, wall-hung sinks were installed. \u201cThis bathroom has no window, but looks bright, large, and attractive,\u201d Marie said.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-18-1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-35343 mb-0 size-chrono\" title=\"shower\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/SWEETEN-Marie-Niarhos-BathKitchen-18-1-723x1085.jpg\" alt=\"Kensington, Brooklyn, home renovation, bathroom renovation, shower head, shower, Brooklyn grandparents\" width=\"723\" height=\"1085\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The renovation was a true collaboration between the homeowners and the architect. Marie explained, \u201cOur Sweeten architect was extremely helpful, making suggestions, listening to our opinions and helping us decide. She seemed to be totally invested while following our tastes and budget.\u201d<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">How do they feel about their new home? \u201cOur new space feels comfortable and cozy,&#8221;\u00a0Marie said. &#8220;The natural light combined with our light fixtures make it a happy place to live. We feel very much at home&#8230;like we have been here for a long time.\u201d<\/p>\n<p><em>Thank you, Marie and John. We hope you\u2019ll have many happy family gatherings in your new home!<\/em><\/p>\n<h4 class=\"p1\"><b>Get even more advice on renovating a home for aging-in-place with Sweeten&#8217;s guides:<\/b><\/h4>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/renovation-101\/guide-aging-in-place-universal-design\/\"><b>A Guide to Aging in Place<\/b><\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"https:\/\/Aging%20in%20Place%20Design%20Costs%20&amp;%20Tips%20to%20Improve%20Home%20Accessibility\"><b>Aging in Place Design Costs &amp; Tips to Improve Home Accessibility<\/b><\